### **Step 2: Configure Server (After Deployment)**

After you run `bash deploy.txt`, the files will be in `/var/www/ubi-support`. Now you need to tell Nginx how to serve them alongside WordPress.

1.  **Open Nginx Config:**
    `sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/wordpress.conf` (or `/default`)

2.  **Add a specific block for the support app:**
    You can either use a **Subdomain** (Recommended) or a **Subfolder**.

    **Option A: Subdomain (e.g., support.ulticonbuildersinc.com)**
    *   Create an A Record in your DNS pointing `support` to your Lightsail IP.
    *   Add this new server block in Nginx:
    ```nginx
    server {
        listen 80;
        server_name support.ulticonbuildersinc.com;
        root /var/www/ubi-support;
        index index.html;
        location / {
            try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
        }
    }
    ```

    **Option B: Subfolder (e.g., ulticonbuildersinc.com/support)**
    *   Edit your existing WordPress server block. Add this inside the `server { ... }` block:
    ```nginx
    location /support {
        alias /var/www/ubi-support;
        try_files $uri $uri/ /support/index.html;
    }
    ```

3.  **Restart Nginx:**
    `sudo systemctl restart nginx
